\section*{Question 10.48}
 \textbf{[2 pts]} A total of \textbf{68 plots} would be required.  We were given a m.e.=10, $\sigma$=50, and z*=\Sexpr{formatC(distrib(0.95,type="q",plot=FALSE),format="f",digits=3)}.  With this, the sample size is calculated with $n=\left(\frac{1.645*50}{10}\right)^{2}$ = $67.65$.  In sample size calculations we always round up.

